ghborhoods. Innovations ranging from recruiting Chinese, Italian, and German police to form “ethnic squads” to the use of deportation and federal immigration restrictions to control local crime—even the introduction of fingerprinting—were motivated by attempts to govern a multiracial city. Campaigns to remake the police department created an urban landscape where power, gender, sexuality, race, ethnicity, crime, and bodies collided and provided a foundation for the supposedly color-blind, technocratic, federally backed, and surveillance-based policing of today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aDiscrimination in law enforcementzNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistory2DLC. 0aDiscrimination in law enforcementzNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistory. 0aLaw enforcementzNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistory2DLC. 0aLaw enforcementzNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistory. 0aPolice brutalityzNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistory2DLC. 0aPolice brutalityzNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistory. 0aPolicezNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistory2DLC. 0aPolicezNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistory. 0aPolice-community relationszNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistory2DLC. 0aPolice-community relationszNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistory. 0aRacial profiling in law enforcementzNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistory2DLC. 0aRacial profiling in law enforcementzNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistory. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311099775008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Engli